  So, basically if you plan on upgrading but can't do so yet (say maybe mid-January you can afford to after the holidays are all over and done with), then the fact you can't play in the meantime is of no concern to them.  If you want a refund for that non-playable period then you lose your account buhbye!<br>
<br>
  From my experience, if your not able to use a service for a lengthy period of time and it's the fault of the company (be it through failed equipment on their end or lack of prior notice to changes made on their end or whatever), then it's good customer relations to reimburse the user for time they were unable to use their service.  Not say sure we'll reimburse you but we're also gonna kick you in the nuts and give you no reason to go on using our service if you make us do that.<br>
<br>
  I think they fucked up pretty bad when they revealed Win95 users would not be able to play.....on the day SoL went live!  Up until that point DX8.0a was going to be the standard (as far as anyone outside Verant knew about that I saw), which is Win95 compatible.  Needing to upgrade memory, video cards, soundcards, etc. is one thing but to throw and OS upgrade on top of that is pretty f'in steep especially at Christmas time.  <br>
<br>
  Luckily I'm at least running Win98, however I'm still unable to play due to my video card not supporting DX8 in general.  So, I'm paying for 2 accounts for the better part of a month that I can't use, and seeing as I'm jobless atm I can't exactly run out and buy a new one.  I was under the impression that I'd still be able to play in the old worlds without SoL installed but since DX8 is required no matter if you have SoL or not I'm still SoL <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (On a side note though, a very good friend of mine is sending me an early x-mas present.  So I should be back in game by the end of the week <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
  So, basically what it boils down to is if you want to continue playing the game deal with it and shut up.  If you no longer wish to continue playing then we'll make sure you have no incentive to come back.  I would think that they'd actually WANT you to come back and play after you had upgraded your system.  The whole point of customer service is to keep your customers coming back to you.  Even if someone did stop playing just to take part of the refund, for one they're not playing anyway so why should they pay for that non-privledge?  Secondly if they do reactivate their account, well that's money coming back into Verant.  They're cutting off a source of revenue instead of leaving a reason for that revenue to come back to them.  Not very good customer relations....though I guess it's about on par for Verant CS.<br>
<br>
